commit.title: Fixing #12223 which was fixing #12152 (locating atomic tactics).
commit.message:
Fixing #12223 which was fixing #12152 (locating atomic tactics).

The update of a loc needs sometimes to override (when calling an Ltac
function), and otherwise to keep the existing loc (assumed to be
fined). We clarify this.

In some situations, overriding was going to a tclOR which was even
setting the loc to a disjoint part of the code.

commit.message:
Fixing #12223 which was fixing #12152 (locating atomic tactics).

The update of a loc needs sometimes to override (when calling an Ltac
function), and otherwise to keep the existing loc (assumed to be
fined). We clarify this.

In some situations, overriding was going to a tclOR which was even
setting the loc to a disjoint part of the code.
